From Heavy Rains In Delhi To Downpour In Goa, Rainfall Updates Across India, You Need To Know

From Goa to West Bengal, multiple Indian states are likely to receive heavy rainfall in the next few days.

by Shreya Ghosh Updated: June 27, 2024

Share

Summer lovers enjoy bragging about the reasons to love the bright sunshine and vibrant days during the warmer months. Sadly, even the biggest fans of this season are exhausted from this summer‚Äôs sweltering heat and intolerable temperatures. We need rainfall to get respite from this harsh weather. The good news is that the present weather conditions are changing and places have started to receive rain. Read on to learn the important rainfall updates nationwide. Parts Of Delhi-NCR Enjoyed Much-Needed Rain On Thursday ‡§Ü‡§ï‡§æ‡§∂‡§µ‡§æ‡§£‡•Ä ‡§∏‡§Æ‡§æ‡§ö‡§æ‡§∞ (@AIRNewsHindi) shared a video of the capital city getting lashed by downpours.

‡§¶‡§ø‡§≤‡•ç‡§≤‡•Ä: ‡§∞‡§æ‡§∑‡•ç‡§ü‡•ç‡§∞‡•Ä‡§Ø ‡§∞‡§æ‡§ú‡§ß‡§æ‡§®‡•Ä ‡§ï‡•ç‡§∑‡•á‡§§‡•ç‡§∞ ‡§ï‡•á ‡§µ‡§ø‡§≠‡§ø‡§®‡•ç‡§® ‡§π‡§ø‡§∏‡•ç‡§∏‡•ã‡§Ç ‡§Æ‡•á‡§Ç ‡§Ü‡§ú ‡§∏‡•Å‡§¨‡§π ‡§π‡§≤‡•ç‡§ï‡•Ä ‡§∏‡•á ‡§Æ‡§ß‡•ç‡§Ø‡§Æ ‡§¨‡§æ‡§∞‡§ø‡§∂ ‡§¶‡§∞‡•ç‡§ú ‡§ï‡•Ä ‡§ó‡§à‡•§#Rain #Delhi pic.twitter.com/18mN7790Og ‚Äî ‡§Ü‡§ï‡§æ‡§∂‡§µ‡§æ‡§£‡•Ä ‡§∏‡§Æ‡§æ‡§ö‡§æ‡§∞ (@AIRNewsHindi) June 27, 2024

Residents of Delhi, Noida, Gurugram, and Ghaziabad woke up to showers and splendid weather as several areas in these places received heavy rainfall. It surely brought a major relief after weeks of unbearable heat and horrifying heatwaves. India Meteorological Department (IMD) already predicted rainfall in parts of the capital city throughout the day. There are expectations for light to moderate-intensity rain and thunderstorms. In addition to this, isolated areas are likely to receive heavy-intensity rainfall and winds with a speed of 20 km/h to 40 km/h in Delhi-NCR, Panipat, Gohana, Gannaur, Sonipat, and nearby places, as shared by RWFC New Delhi on X.

The monsoons are finally here and the bounteous rains are being welcomed with open hearts. Delhi Rain üåßÔ∏è‚òîüåü‚ù§Ô∏èü©µ pic.twitter.com/zIOD664JOL ‚Äî Hrudananda Prusty || ‡§π‡•É‡§¶‡§æ‡§®‡§®‡•ç‡§¶ ‡§™‡•É‡§∑‡•ç‡§ü‡§ø üáÆüá≥ (@AapkaHrudananda) June 27, 2024

Though it has started to rain in Delhi, the monsoon season is still yet to make a grand entry here. According to a report by NDTV, it is likely that the monsoon will reach the capital city by this week-end. It is expected to begin by June 29 or June 30. Also read: No Proper Drainage System In Ram Temple, Ayodhya? Months After Inauguration, Chief Priest Complains About Leaking Roofs Rainfall Updates In Other Parts Of India

Picture credit- Canva IMD issued a press release on Wednesday stating the rainfall predictions for multiple places in India in the next few days. Coastal Karnataka, south interior Karnataka, Kerala, Mahe, Tamil Nadu, Haryana, East Rajasthan, Bihar, Odisha, Uttarakhand, Uttar Pradesh, sub-Himalayan West Bengal, Goa, Konkan, and Northeastern states are likely to receive isolated heavy to very heavy rainfall. According to a report by Hindustan Times, the department has also issued warnings for the change in weather. Heavy rainfall will likely lash Goa, coastal Karnataka, and South Maharashtra on June 27. Arunachal Pradesh may receive rainfall during the night hours. On June 28, there are chances for heavy to very heavy rain in Arunachal Pradesh, Goa, Kandla Port, and some areas in Assam and West Bengal, according to a report by The Weather Channel. Also read: Switzerland: Heavy Rainfall Causes Floods &#038; Landslides; Temporarily Disrupts Rail Services In Zermatt These are all the recent rainfall updates in different parts of the country. Cover Image Courtesy: X/ ‡§Ü‡§ï‡§æ‡§∂‡§µ‡§æ‡§£‡•Ä ‡§∏‡§Æ‡§æ‡§ö‡§æ‡§∞ (@AIRNewsHindi)  For more such snackable content, interesting discoveries and the latest updates on food, travel and experiences in your city, download the Curly Tales App. Download HERE.

